    <fr:title text="The positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected › "><fr:link href="jms-0028.xml" title="The positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected" addr="jms-0028" type="local">The positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected</fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i,j]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="jms-001M.xml" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001M" type="local">positive</fr:link> elements of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex>; we must show that there exists a positive element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k\in  I]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\sqsubseteq  k]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j\sqsubseteq  k]]></fr:tex>. This follows immediately from the directedness of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> and <fr:link href="jms-0029.xml" title="Positivity is upward-closed" addr="jms-0029" type="local">the fact that positivity is monotone</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
