            <fr:title text="Positivity is upward-closed">Positivity is upward-closed</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\sqsubseteq  j]]></fr:tex> in a <fr:link href="jms-001S.xml" title="Pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001S" type="local">pointed</fr:link> dcpo <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-001M.xml" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001M" type="local">positive</fr:link>; then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-001M.xml" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001M" type="local">positive</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>6970</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/5932</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-5932.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Fixing semidirected <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j\sqsubseteq  \bigsqcup {J}]]></fr:tex>, we must show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J]]></fr:tex> is inhabited. This follows from our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> is positive becuase <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\sqsubseteq  j\sqsubseteq  \bigsqcup {J}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
